We are awaiting biopsies to confirm whether this is adenocarcinoma.  This will also help for deciding on extent of invasion.  Further, patient will undergo a CT-scan of the abdomen and pelvis evaluating for regional spread and metastasis.  He will also undergo testing for CEA for prognosis.  He has a history of stable nodules in the lung.  He has a 30-pack-year history of smoking, stopped about 25 years ago.  We will order a chest x-ray, PA and lateral, and he will also be seen by one of our colorectal surgery colleagues.  I will see the patient back after this workup.

